26/11/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Former Turkish Foreign Minister and Parliament Speaker Hikmet Cetin will meet with NATO Secretary General Lord George Robertson in Brussels before the end of this month. 
They will discuss details of Cetin's new appointment as NATO's senior civilian representative in Afghanistan.
In other developments, Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul travels to Italy on Thursday to attend a meeting of EU foreign ministers on the sidelines of an international conference in Naples. 
Gul vowed Tuesday that despite recent terrorist attacks in Istanbul, Turkey would not back down from economic and political reforms aimed at democratising the country. 
(Anadolu Agency, TRT 2, NTV - 25/11/03)
